â€¢â€¢Submitting Formsâ€¢â€¢

1. The first and most known way is to click the submit button. After the user clicks the button it then send a Request to the URL.

Â°Â°ExampleÂ°Â°
<button>Submit</button>

ğŸš¨ Note:
Â°Â°Â°To disable the default Submit behavior, we can add 
"type="button" 
to the <button>. This will tell the Browser that the "<button>" shouldnt be submitted to that given form.Â°Â°Â°

Â°Â°Â°We can also use the <input> element with type="submit" for a option, instead of using  a <button> element. This input looks and behaves no different then a <button>. Basically instead of using the <label> element toâœ¨ describe the <input>. Instead we use the value attribute.Â°Â°Â°ğŸ¦¸
Â°Â°Example
<input type="submit" value="Submit">
